 We find that over a significant range of parameters the\nproton component is generally less prominent than the primary electron\ncomponent. We discuss the prospects for the detection of the X-ray and GeV\nsignatures of the mildly relativistic outflow of hypernovae.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 Aug 2008 20:00:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2010-11-11"}
